<I>"Show me a good mouser and I'll show you a cat with bad breath" -- Garfield</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/31/01 11:16:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> This is the last one ..</span><hr size=1> .. on this thread.  Chip, you haven't proved or disproved anything.  You keep dodging the points I've brought up.  If you want to know the specific quest, talk to the Vah Shir that posted.  Exploitive: hiring others, using a mule, using a second comp, vendor mining.  Some more, some less.  All permissable, but most not within the spirit of solving a quest directly.<br>
<br>
An example: monk trainer says &quot;You must prove yourself worthy.  Go forth, kill orc pawns, bring me their scalps!&quot;  Scalps don't TLC, but just imagine that they do for argument's sake.  You stop by a vendor, buy 4 scalps, and return them.  This is the least &quot;exploitive&quot; method of dodging TLC.  You did the quest, but it wasn't quite what the trainer told you to do, now was it?<br>
<br>
A more real example.  Suppose you are doing the monk shackle quest from scatch.  One clue is along the lines of &quot;we need the hand of Tynn&quot;.  Hmm.  Not very descriptive.  So, you kill things all over.  If you are very very lucky indeed, you will hunt in Kurns and kill fingerbone skeletons and a finger bone will drop.  If you are even luckier, you will save it and have someone identify it.  If you are luckier still, you will realize it's significance and go back to farm more until you have a full set.  More likely, you will have missed all this and leveled past the TLC barrier and never ever solve the quest because TLC would have denied you even the clues to solve it.<br>
<br>
Then there are the quests that are bugged.  Many are buggy.  You know what you need, but it doesn't drop or you're not quite sure if you have the right MOB/s.  What do you do?  Level or wait?  For most bugs, you can leisurely level to 60 before it's fixed.  Do you then delevel to do the quest?  Use a second comp?  Pay a lowbie to test to see if it's fixed -- this may mean a 20 hour camp just to test it (ie. 5-10k plat).<br>
<br>
It's not that TLC literally makes completion impossible, it's that it makes solving impossible and makes completion a nightmare.  Not every quest is worthy of epic effort to complete.  In fact, most aren't.  That's why TLC kills off discovery here.  Because most aren't worth it, it behoves one to wait for the solution before taking the plunge.  It encourages folks to wait for others to do all the work and post a spoiler.<br>
<br>
For the other points, read my post on the other thread. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=986.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=986.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=935.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=991.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=43><img src=http://www.firiona-vie.com/images/arfv.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=986.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=986.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=986.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox<option value="firionaviefrm10">A Bard for a Day<option value="firionaviefrm23">Hero Heart Tavern<opt